{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Amongst all the troubling deficits we struggle with today --"},{"time":3000,"text":"we think of financial and economic primarily --"},{"time":6000,"text":"the ones that concern me most"},{"time":8000,"text":"is the deficit of political dialogue --"},{"time":10000,"text":"our ability to address modern conflicts"},{"time":12000,"text":"as they are,"},{"time":14000,"text":"to go to the source of what they're all about"},{"time":17000,"text":"and to understand the key players"},{"time":19000,"text":"and to deal with them."},{"time":21000,"text":"We who are diplomats,"},{"time":23000,"text":"we are trained to deal with conflicts between states and issues between states."},{"time":26000,"text":"And I can tell you, our agenda is full."},{"time":29000,"text":"There is trade, there is disarmament,"},{"time":31000,"text":"there is cross-border relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34000,"text":"But the picture is changing,"},{"time":36000,"text":"and we are seeing that there are new key players"},{"time":39000,"text":"coming onto the scene."},{"time":41000,"text":"We loosely call them \"groups.\""},{"time":44000,"text":"They may represent social, religious,"},{"time":47000,"text":"political, economic, military realities."},{"time":50000,"text":"And we struggle with how to deal with them."},{"time":52000,"text":"The rules of engagement:"},{"time":54000,"text":"how to talk, when to talk,"},{"time":56000,"text":"and how to deal with them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"Let me show you a slide here"},{"time":61000,"text":"which illustrates the character of conflicts"},{"time":63000,"text":"since 1946 until today."},{"time":65000,"text":"You see the green"},{"time":67000,"text":"is a traditional interstate conflict,"},{"time":70000,"text":"the ones we used to read about."},{"time":73000,"text":"The red is modern conflict,"},{"time":75000,"text":"conflicts within states."},{"time":78000,"text":"These are quite different,"},{"time":80000,"text":"and they are outside the grasp"},{"time":83000,"text":"of modern diplomacy."},{"time":86000,"text":"And the core of these key actors"},{"time":88000,"text":"are groups"},{"time":90000,"text":"who represent different interests"},{"time":92000,"text":"inside countries."},{"time":94000,"text":"And the way they deal with their conflicts rapidly spreads to other countries."},{"time":97000,"text":"So in a way, it is everybody's business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"Another acknowledgment we've seen during these years,"},{"time":103000,"text":"recent years,"},{"time":105000,"text":"is that very few"},{"time":107000,"text":"of these domestic interstate, intrastate conflicts"},{"time":111000,"text":"can be solved militarily."},{"time":113000,"text":"They may have to be dealt with with military means,"},{"time":115000,"text":"but they cannot be solved by military means."},{"time":118000,"text":"They need political solutions."},{"time":120000,"text":"And we, therefore, have a problem,"},{"time":122000,"text":"because they escape traditional diplomacy."},{"time":125000,"text":"And we have among states"},{"time":127000,"text":"a reluctance in dealing with them."},{"time":129000,"text":"Plus, during the last decade,"},{"time":131000,"text":"we've been in the mode"},{"time":133000,"text":"where dealing with groups"},{"time":135000,"text":"was conceptually and politically dangerous."},{"time":138000,"text":"After 9/11,"},{"time":140000,"text":"either you were with us or against us."},{"time":142000,"text":"It was black or white."},{"time":144000,"text":"And groups are very often"},{"time":146000,"text":"immediately label terrorists."},{"time":148000,"text":"And who would talk to terrorists?"},{"time":151000,"text":"The West, as I would see it,"},{"time":153000,"text":"comes out of that decade weakened,"},{"time":155000,"text":"because we didn't understand the group."},{"time":158000,"text":"So we've spent more time"},{"time":160000,"text":"on focusing on why we should not talk to others"},{"time":163000,"text":"than finding out how we talk to others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"Now I'm not naive."},{"time":168000,"text":"You cannot talk to everybody all the time."},{"time":170000,"text":"And there are times you should walk."},{"time":173000,"text":"And sometimes military intervention is necessary."},{"time":175000,"text":"I happen to believe that Libya was necessary"},{"time":178000,"text":"and that military intervention in Afghanistan was also necessary."},{"time":181000,"text":"And my country relies on its security"},{"time":184000,"text":"through military alliance, that's clear."},{"time":187000,"text":"But still we have a large deficit"},{"time":190000,"text":"in dealing with and understanding modern conflict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":192000,"text":"Let us turn to Afghanistan."},{"time":195000,"text":"10 years after that military intervention,"},{"time":197000,"text":"that country is far from secure."},{"time":199000,"text":"The situation, to be honest, is very serious."},{"time":202000,"text":"Now again, the military is necessary,"},{"time":205000,"text":"but the military is no problem-solver."},{"time":208000,"text":"When I first came to Afghanistan in 2005 as a foreign minister,"},{"time":211000,"text":"I met the commander of ISAF,"},{"time":213000,"text":"the international troops."},{"time":215000,"text":"And he told me that, \"This can be won militarily, minister."},{"time":218000,"text":"We just have to persevere.\""},{"time":221000,"text":"Now four COM ISAF's later,"},{"time":223000,"text":"we hear a different message:"},{"time":225000,"text":"\"This cannot be won militarily."},{"time":227000,"text":"We need military presence,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but we need to move to politics."},{"time":231000,"text":"We can only solve this through a political solution."},{"time":234000,"text":"And it is not us who will solve it;"},{"time":237000,"text":"Afghans have to solve it.\""},{"time":239000,"text":"But then they need a different political process"},{"time":241000,"text":"than the one they were given in 2001, 2002."},{"time":245000,"text":"They need an inclusive process"},{"time":248000,"text":"where the real fabric of this very complicated society"},{"time":251000,"text":"can deal with their issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"Everybody seems to agree with that."},{"time":255000,"text":"It was very controversial to say three, four, five years ago."},{"time":258000,"text":"Now everybody agrees."},{"time":260000,"text":"But now, as we prepare to talk,"},{"time":263000,"text":"we understand how little we know."},{"time":265000,"text":"Because we didn't talk."},{"time":267000,"text":"We didn't grasp what was going on."},{"time":270000,"text":"The International Committee of the Red Cross, the ICRC,"},{"time":273000,"text":"is talking to everyone,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and it is doing so because it is neutral."},{"time":278000,"text":"And that's one reason why"},{"time":280000,"text":"that organization probably"},{"time":282000,"text":"is the best informed key player"},{"time":284000,"text":"to understand modern conflict --"},{"time":286000,"text":"because they talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288000,"text":"My point is that you don't have to be neutral to talk."},{"time":292000,"text":"And you don't have to agree"},{"time":294000,"text":"when you sit down with the other side."},{"time":296000,"text":"And you can always walk."},{"time":299000,"text":"But if you don't talk,"},{"time":301000,"text":"you can't engage the other side."},{"time":303000,"text":"And the other side which you're going to engage"},{"time":305000,"text":"is the one with whom you profoundly disagree."},{"time":308000,"text":"Prime Minister Rabin said when he engaged the Oslo process,"},{"time":311000,"text":"\"You don't make peace with your friends,"},{"time":313000,"text":"you make peace with your enemies.\""},{"time":315000,"text":"It's hard, but it is necessary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"Let me go one step further."},{"time":320000,"text":"This is Tahrir Square."},{"time":322000,"text":"There's a revolution going on."},{"time":324000,"text":"The Arab Spring is heading into fall"},{"time":326000,"text":"and is moving into winter."},{"time":328000,"text":"It will last for a long, long time."},{"time":331000,"text":"And who knows what it will be called in the end."},{"time":334000,"text":"That's not the point."},{"time":336000,"text":"The point is that we are probably seeing,"},{"time":339000,"text":"for the first time in the history of the Arab world,"},{"time":341000,"text":"a revolution bottom-up --"},{"time":343000,"text":"people's revolution."},{"time":345000,"text":"Social groups are taking to the streets."},{"time":348000,"text":"And we find out in the West"},{"time":350000,"text":"that we know very little about what's happening."},{"time":353000,"text":"Because we never talk to the people in these countries."},{"time":357000,"text":"Most governments followed"},{"time":359000,"text":"the dictate of the authoritarian leaders"},{"time":361000,"text":"to stay away from these different groups,"},{"time":363000,"text":"because they were terrorists."},{"time":367000,"text":"So now that they are emerging in the street"},{"time":369000,"text":"and we salute the democratic revolution,"},{"time":372000,"text":"we find out how little we know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"Right now, the discussion goes,"},{"time":376000,"text":"\"Should we talk to the Muslim Brotherhood?"},{"time":379000,"text":"Should we talk to Hamas?"},{"time":381000,"text":"If we talk to them, we may legitimize them.\""},{"time":384000,"text":"I think that is wrong."},{"time":386000,"text":"If you talk in the right way, you make it very clear"},{"time":388000,"text":"that talking is not agreeing."},{"time":391000,"text":"And how can we tell the Muslim Brotherhood,"},{"time":393000,"text":"as we should,"},{"time":395000,"text":"that they must respect minority rights,"},{"time":399000,"text":"if we don't accept majority rights?"},{"time":402000,"text":"Because they may turn out to be a majority."},{"time":405000,"text":"How can we escape [having] a double-standard,"},{"time":408000,"text":"if we at the same time preach democracy"},{"time":411000,"text":"and at the same time"},{"time":413000,"text":"don't want to deal with the groups that are representative?"},{"time":415000,"text":"How will we ever be interlocutors?"},{"time":418000,"text":"Now my diplomats are instructed"},{"time":420000,"text":"to talk to all these groups."},{"time":422000,"text":"But talking can be done in different ways."},{"time":425000,"text":"We make a distinction between talking from a diplomatic level"},{"time":428000,"text":"and talking at the political level."},{"time":431000,"text":"Now talking can be accompanied with aid or not with aid."},{"time":434000,"text":"Talking can be accompanied with inclusion or not inclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"There's a big array"},{"time":439000,"text":"of the ways of dealing with this."},{"time":441000,"text":"So if we refuse"},{"time":443000,"text":"to talk to these new groups"},{"time":446000,"text":"that are going to be dominating the news in years to come,"},{"time":449000,"text":"we will further radicalization,"},{"time":451000,"text":"I believe."},{"time":453000,"text":"We will make the road from violent activities into politics"},{"time":456000,"text":"harder to travel."},{"time":458000,"text":"And if we cannot demonstrate to these groups"},{"time":461000,"text":"that if you move towards democracy,"},{"time":463000,"text":"if you move towards taking part"},{"time":466000,"text":"in civilized and normal standards among states,"},{"time":469000,"text":"there are some rewards on the other side."},{"time":472000,"text":"The paradox here"},{"time":474000,"text":"is that the last decade probably was a lost decade"},{"time":477000,"text":"for making progress on this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479000,"text":"And the paradox is that the decade before the last decade was so promising --"},{"time":483000,"text":"and for one reason primarily."},{"time":486000,"text":"And the reason is what happened in South Africa:"},{"time":488000,"text":"Nelson Mandela."},{"time":490000,"text":"When Mandela came out of prison"},{"time":492000,"text":"after 27 years of captivity,"},{"time":495000,"text":"if he had told his people,"},{"time":497000,"text":"\"It's time to take up the arms,"},{"time":499000,"text":"it's time to fight,\""},{"time":501000,"text":"he would have been followed."},{"time":503000,"text":"And I think the international community"},{"time":505000,"text":"would have said, \"Fair enough."},{"time":507000,"text":"It's their right to fight.\""},{"time":509000,"text":"Now as you know, Mandela didn't do that."},{"time":512000,"text":"In his memoirs, \"Long Road to Freedom,\""},{"time":515000,"text":"he wrote that he survived"},{"time":517000,"text":"during those years of captivity"},{"time":520000,"text":"because he always decided to look upon his oppressor"},{"time":523000,"text":"as also being a human being,"},{"time":526000,"text":"also being a human being."},{"time":529000,"text":"So he engaged a political process of dialogue,"},{"time":534000,"text":"not as a strategy of the weak,"},{"time":537000,"text":"but as a strategy of the strong."},{"time":540000,"text":"And he engaged talking profoundly"},{"time":543000,"text":"by settling some of the most tricky issues"},{"time":545000,"text":"through a truth and reconciliation process"},{"time":548000,"text":"where people came and talked."},{"time":550000,"text":"Now South African friends will know"},{"time":552000,"text":"that was very painful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554000,"text":"So what can we learn from all of this?"},{"time":557000,"text":"Dialogue is not easy --"},{"time":559000,"text":"not between individuals, not between groups, not between governments --"},{"time":562000,"text":"but it is very necessary."},{"time":565000,"text":"If we're going to deal with political conflict-solving of conflicts,"},{"time":569000,"text":"if we're going to understand these new groups"},{"time":572000,"text":"which are coming from bottom-up,"},{"time":575000,"text":"supported by technology, which is available to all,"},{"time":578000,"text":"we diplomats cannot be sitting back in the banquets"},{"time":581000,"text":"believing that we are doing interstate relations."},{"time":584000,"text":"We have to connect"},{"time":586000,"text":"with these profound changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"And what is dialogue really about?"},{"time":590000,"text":"When I enter into dialogue,"},{"time":592000,"text":"I really hope that the other side"},{"time":594000,"text":"would pick up my points of view,"},{"time":596000,"text":"that I would impress upon them"},{"time":598000,"text":"my opinions and my values."},{"time":600000,"text":"I cannot do that"},{"time":602000,"text":"unless I send the signals that I will be open"},{"time":604000,"text":"to listen to the other side's signals."},{"time":607000,"text":"We need a lot more training on how to do that"},{"time":610000,"text":"and a lot more practice"},{"time":612000,"text":"on how that can take problem-solving forward."},{"time":615000,"text":"We know from our personal experiences"},{"time":617000,"text":"that it's easy sometimes"},{"time":619000,"text":"just to walk,"},{"time":621000,"text":"and sometimes you may need to fight."},{"time":624000,"text":"And I wouldn't say that is the wrong thing in all circumstances."},{"time":627000,"text":"Sometimes you have to."},{"time":629000,"text":"But that strategy seldom takes you very far."},{"time":632000,"text":"The alternative is a strategy"},{"time":634000,"text":"of engagement and principled dialogue."},{"time":636000,"text":"And I believe we need to strengthen this approach"},{"time":639000,"text":"in modern diplomacy,"},{"time":641000,"text":"not only between states,"},{"time":643000,"text":"but also within states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"We are seeing some new signs."},{"time":647000,"text":"We could never have done"},{"time":649000,"text":"the convention against anti-personnel landmines"},{"time":651000,"text":"and the convention that is banning cluster munitions"},{"time":655000,"text":"unless we had done diplomacy differently,"},{"time":658000,"text":"by engaging with civil society."},{"time":660000,"text":"All of a sudden,"},{"time":662000,"text":"NGOs were not only standing in the streets, crying their slogans,"},{"time":665000,"text":"but they were taking [them] into the negotiations,"},{"time":668000,"text":"partly because they represented the victims of these weapons."},{"time":672000,"text":"And they brought their knowledge."},{"time":674000,"text":"And there was an interaction"},{"time":676000,"text":"between diplomacy and the power coming bottom-up."},{"time":679000,"text":"This is perhaps a first element"},{"time":681000,"text":"of a change."},{"time":683000,"text":"In the future, I believe,"},{"time":685000,"text":"we should draw examples from these different illustrations,"},{"time":688000,"text":"not to have diplomacy"},{"time":690000,"text":"which is disconnected from people and civil society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"And we have to go also"},{"time":696000,"text":"beyond traditional diplomacy"},{"time":698000,"text":"to the survival issue of our times,"},{"time":700000,"text":"climate change."},{"time":702000,"text":"How are we going to solve climate change through negotiations,"},{"time":705000,"text":"unless we are able to make civil society and people,"},{"time":708000,"text":"not part of the problem, but part of the solution?"},{"time":711000,"text":"It is going to demand an inclusive process of diplomacy"},{"time":714000,"text":"very different from the one we are practicing today"},{"time":717000,"text":"as we are heading to new rounds of difficult climate negotiations,"},{"time":720000,"text":"but when we move toward something"},{"time":722000,"text":"which has to be much more"},{"time":724000,"text":"along a broad mobilization."},{"time":726000,"text":"It's crucial to understand, I believe,"},{"time":729000,"text":"because of technology and because of globalization,"},{"time":731000,"text":"societies from bottom-up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733000,"text":"We as diplomats"},{"time":735000,"text":"need to know the social capital"},{"time":737000,"text":"of communities."},{"time":739000,"text":"What is it that makes people trust each other,"},{"time":742000,"text":"not only between states,"},{"time":744000,"text":"but also within states?"},{"time":746000,"text":"What is the legitimacy of diplomacy,"},{"time":749000,"text":"of the the solution we devise as diplomats"},{"time":752000,"text":"if they cannot be reflected and understood"},{"time":755000,"text":"by also these broader forces of societies"},{"time":758000,"text":"that we now very loosely call groups?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"The good thing is that we are not powerless."},{"time":765000,"text":"We have never had"},{"time":767000,"text":"as many means of communication,"},{"time":769000,"text":"means of being connected, means of reaching out,"},{"time":772000,"text":"means of including."},{"time":774000,"text":"The diplomatic toolbox"},{"time":776000,"text":"is actually full of different tools we can use"},{"time":779000,"text":"to strengthen our communication."},{"time":781000,"text":"But the problem is that we are coming out of a decade"},{"time":784000,"text":"where we had a fear of touching it."},{"time":786000,"text":"Now, I hope, in the coming years,"},{"time":789000,"text":"that we are able to demonstrate through some concrete examples"},{"time":792000,"text":"that fear is receding"},{"time":795000,"text":"and that we can take courage"},{"time":797000,"text":"from that alliance"},{"time":799000,"text":"with civil society"},{"time":801000,"text":"in different countries"},{"time":803000,"text":"to support their problem-solving,"},{"time":805000,"text":"among the Afghans,"},{"time":807000,"text":"inside the Palestinian population,"},{"time":810000,"text":"between the peoples of Palestine and Israel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"And as we try to understand this broad movement"},{"time":815000,"text":"across the Arab world,"},{"time":817000,"text":"we are not powerless."},{"time":819000,"text":"We need to improve the necessary skills,"},{"time":821000,"text":"and we need the courage to use them."},{"time":823000,"text":"In my country,"},{"time":825000,"text":"I have seen how the council of Islamist groups"},{"time":830000,"text":"and Christian groups"},{"time":832000,"text":"came together, not as a government initiative,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but they came together on their own initiative"},{"time":837000,"text":"to establish contact and dialogue"},{"time":839000,"text":"in times where things were pretty low-key tension."},{"time":843000,"text":"And when tension increased,"},{"time":845000,"text":"they already had that dialogue,"},{"time":848000,"text":"and that was a strength to deal with different issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851000,"text":"Our modern Western societies"},{"time":853000,"text":"are more complex than before,"},{"time":855000,"text":"in this time of migration."},{"time":857000,"text":"How are we going to settle and build a bigger \"We\""},{"time":860000,"text":"to deal with our issues"},{"time":862000,"text":"if we don't improve our skills of communication?"},{"time":864000,"text":"So there are many reasons,"},{"time":866000,"text":"and for all of these reasons,"},{"time":868000,"text":"this is time and this is why we must talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}